caption: World mental health day 💙 You all know mental health is a topic very close to my heart. Every day, I get comments and messages from people all around the world talking about their experiences and what they’re going through, and for me - hearing your stories is one of the greatest gifts of what I get to do. I’m not the biggest fan of social media in it’s entirety (as you also know), but what I do love is that it’s a place where we can all be brought together. Not just today, but every day I’m wishing you every ounce of love, and want to remind you that even if you don’t feel supported in the community that you live in now, you have a community here. #worldsmentalhealthday

Bye tiff 👋 Thanks for a wild 36 hours, and all the love towards Knives Out

Last night was unreal..✨✨
Three years ago I came to TIFF with my agents, I was filming my first project and no one knew who I was - and I remember standing outside, behind the barricades, watching Matthew McConaughey and Scarlett Johansson arrive at the premiere of the big film for that year...I remember thinking to myself, “How incredible would it be to have a film here one day?” Last night, as we pulled up to the theater, I saw the exact spot where I was standing three years ago, and got to experience my first film festival premiere at that same theatre. Thank you so much to everyone who came out last night for making this screening so special ❤️ and thank you to the brilliant and wonderful @riancjohnson for having me be a part of this film amongst this incredible cast 🔪 #tiff #knivesout
